#: ../../../about/deprecated.rst:47
msgid "Plugin argument passing through ``arg=<string>`` (since 6.1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about/deprecated.rst:49
msgid ""
"Passing TCG plugins arguments through ``arg=`` is redundant is makes the "
"command-line less readable, especially when the argument itself consist of a "
"name and a value, e.g. ``-plugin plugin_name,arg=\"arg_name=arg_value\"``. "
"Therefore, the usage of ``arg`` is redundant. Single-word arguments are "
"treated as short-form boolean values, and passed to plugins as "
"``arg_name=on``. However, short-form booleans are deprecated and full "
"explicit ``arg_name=on`` form is preferred."
msgstr ""

